The U.S. Chamber of Commerce is highlighting the issue of military spouse unemployment, which is currently more than seven times the national rate. The Chamber acknowledges that military spouses face challenges such as frequent relocations and the difficulty of maintaining a career. They emphasize the need for businesses to make significant changes to address this issue. The Chamber urges companies to create flexible, transferable, and remote work opportunities to support military spouses. They believe that tapping into the skills and loyalty of military spouses can benefit organizations. The Chamber calls on businesses to join the Military Spouse Employment Advisory Council, share best practices, and collaborate with organizations like Hiring Our Heroes. They emphasize that supporting military families is critical for national security and urge companies to prioritize this issue.